<h1>Button Groups</h1>

<p>The button group component is used to group buttons togther.</p>
<p>It uses contextual components, so if you render buttons or button links inside a group, the button components will inherit the groups <em>disabled</em>, <em>inline</em> & <em>mini</em> properties.</p>

<h2>Usage</h2>

<p>Let's look at a basic example:</p>

{{#docs-demo as |demo|}}

  {{#demo.example name="button-group"}}

    {{#uxs-button-group align=align disabled=disabled inline=inline mini=mini as |group|}}
      {{group.button "Save"}}
      {{group.button "Save & Publish"}}
      {{group.link "Cancel" "docs.forms.buttons"}}
    {{/uxs-button-group}}
  {{/demo.example}}

  {{demo.snippet 'button-group.hbs'}}

{{/docs-demo}}

